```mermaid
graph TD
    subgraph Tier3 [@mariozechner/pi-coding-agent]
        CA[pi-coding-agent]
        EXT[Extensions<br/>load via jiti]
    end

    subgraph Tier2 [@mariozechner/pi-agent-core]
        AC[pi-agent-core]
    end

    subgraph Tier1 [@mariozechner/pi-ai]
        AI[pi-ai]
    end

    subgraph Support [Supporting Packages]
        TUI[pi-tui]
    end

    CA --> AC
    AC --> AI
    CA --> TUI

    EXT -->|imports| CA
    EXT -->|imports| AC
    EXT -->|imports| AI
    EXT -->|imports| TUI

    CA -->|provides| EXT[ExtensionAPI]

    style EXT fill:#e1f5e1,stroke:#4caf50,stroke-width:2px
    style CA fill:#e1f5e1
    style AC fill:#e1f5e1
    style AI fill:#e1f5e1
    style TUI fill:#f5e1e1

    classDef tier3 fill:#c8e6c9,stroke:#388e3c,stroke-width:2px
    classDef tier2 fill:#c5cae9,stroke:#3f51b5,stroke-width:2px
    classDef tier1 fill:#ffccbc,stroke:#d84315,stroke-width:2px
    classDef support fill:#fff9c4,stroke:#fbc02d,stroke-width:2px
    classDef ext fill:#dcedc8,stroke:#689f38,stroke-width:2px

    class CA tier3
    class AC tier2
    class AI tier1
    class TUI support
    class EXT ext
```

---

**Explanation**:
- Extensions are user-loaded code (TypeScript) that import from pi packages (coding-agent, agent-core, ai, tui) to use APIs.
- `ExtensionAPI` is provided by `pi-coding-agent` to extensions.
- Extensions run in the same process (no sandbox), so they can call any pi API.
- Dependencies direction: extensions depend on pi packages (not vice versa). This is safe because extensions are plug-ins.
- Extensions do NOT create new package dependencies for the core packages; they are optional and loaded at runtime.
- Hot-reload: extensions can be reloaded without restarting the whole app (they are re-instantiated).
